               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿĀlamgīr'nāmah by Muḥammad Kāẓim ibn Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85135483 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064913" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_485x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3257">ʿĀlamgīr'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3257">عالم گير نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Substantial fragment from a fine copy of the official regnal chronicle commissioned by the Timurid Emperor <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658575.0x000001 viaf_6178410" role="pat">ʿĀlamgīr I</persName>, written by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656382.0x000001 viaf_155145541808496601063" role="aut">Munshīʾ Muḥammad Kāẓim</persName> (d. 1092/1681), son of the historian for <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656355.0x000001 viaf_13108102" role="subject">Emperor Shāh Jahān I</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_15147663108860552472" role="aut">Munshīʾ ‘Amīnā’ Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The annalist chronicle covers the war of succession leading to the overthrow of Emperor Shāh Jahān I, and <persName key="viaf_6178410" role="subject">Prince Muḥammad Awrangzīb Bahādur</persName>’s accession to the throne as emperor, followed by the first ten regnal years. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat calligraphic nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped and Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Binding damaged (front board consists of combed marble paper with brown leather edging over delaminating and crumbling pasteboard; back board consists of deep brown leather over delaminating and crumbling pasteboard, revealing Kaithi texts), labels. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; wormholes, cropped, light water stains, creased and stained edges, powdered chalk interspersed throughout. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_155145541808496601063">Muḥammad Kāẓim ibn Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_155145541808496601063">محمّد كاظم ابن محمّد امين ابن ابو الحسين القزوينى</persName>
